    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-08-28T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-08-28T17:00:00-05:00" n="290"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d290">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.24/569: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-08-28T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 28, 1941—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>544. Your 1319, August 27, 4 p.m. and 1322, August 27, 7 p.m. [Here follows
                    report based on memorandum by the Secretary of <pb facs="0414" n="406"
                        xml:id="pg_406"/> State, August 27, 1941, printed in <ref
                        target="frus1931-41v02#pg_569">
                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, volume II, page
                        569</ref>.]</p>
                <p>In the evening the Japanese Ambassador called at my apartment in connection with
                    another matter and I took the occasion to emphasize again what I had previously
                    said. The Ambassador said that he had already reported to his Government what I
                    had said and that he had recommended that the Japanese Government purchase oil
                    in this country in accordance with the suggestion brought out in our earlier
                    conversation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
